The city's disaster management team is helping hundreds of families find alternative accommodation after over a hundred shacks were razed to the ground on Monday night. Courtesy #DStv403 KEMPTON PARK - Ekurhuleni's disaster management team is helping hundreds of families find alternative accommodation
after over a hundred shacks were razed to the ground last night. READ: Kempton park fire affects almost 900 people The fire broke out at around seven in the Max informal settlement in Pomona, Kempton Park, and was extinguished shortly after midnight. Emergency services spokesperson, William Ntladi said social workers, Red Cross, and Home Affairs representatives are on-site to assist people with accommodation and the replacement of key documents. Ntladi stated the firefighters' main focus was preventing loss of life and suppressing the blaze that was being spread by a strong wind.